<h2>Licensing Rules</h2>
<p>If you wish to operate in the State of Texas, you must receive a license from the Department. To be licensed, please submit a new application and fee to the Department. Operating in Texas without a license is a Prohibited Act under Texas law, punishable by a penalty of up to $25,000 per day, per violation, or referral to the Attorney General for injunctive relief to prohibit operating without a license, civil penalties, attorney’s fees and costs.</p>
